      "text": [
        ": \"خَيْرُ نِسَائِكُمُ اَلَّتِي إِنْ غَضِبَتْ أَوْ أَغْضَبَتْ قَالَتْ لِزَوْجِهَا يَدِي فِي يَدِكَ لاَ أَكْتَحِلُ بِغُمْضٍ حَتَّى تَرْضَى عَنِّي\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4366 - Jamil ibn Darraj narrated from Abu Abdillah (as) who said: \"The best of your women is the one who, if she becomes angry or causes her husband to become angry, says to him, 'My hand is in your hand, and I will not rest until you are pleased with me.'\""
        ]
      }
